===Etymology===
From {{PIE.|la}} ''*ad-'' ("[[to]]", "[[near]]", or "[[at]]"). The English word ''[[at]]'' is a [[cognate]].

===Preposition===
{{infl|la|preposition}} (+ {{acc}})

# (''direction'') [[toward]], [[to]], [[up to]] 
#: denoting a [[vertical]] direction:
#:* ''[[w:Lucretius|Lucretius]]'', from the fourth book of ''[[w:De Rerum Natura|De Rerum Natura]]''
#:*: ''[[fugere|Fugere]] '''ad''' [[puppis|puppim]] [[collis|colles]] [[campus#Latin|campi]][[-que|que]] [[videre|videntur]].''
#:*:: The [[hill]]s and [[field]]s [[appear]] to [[fly]] '''toward''' the [[ship]].
#:* ''[[w:Pliny the Elder|Pliny the Elder]]'', from book II of ''[[w:Naturalis Historia|Naturalis Historia]]''
#:*: ''[[meridies|Meridie]] [[umbra]]e [[cadere|cadunt]] '''ad''' [[septentrio]]nem, [[ortus|ortu]] [[vero]] '''ad''' [[occasus|occasum]].''
#:*:: At [[noon]] the [[shadow]]s [[fall]] '''towards''' the [[north]], [and] at [[sunrise]], point '''to''' the [[west]].
#:: ''[[animus|Animus]] [[alius]] '''ad''' [[alius|alia]] [[vitium|vitia]] propensior.''
#:in a direction [[upwards]], frequent in works of poets
#::''[[manus|Manus]][[-que|que]] [[sursum]] '''ad''' [[caelus|caelum]] [[tollere|sustulit]].''
#:::'''And''' on high [[hand]]s he [[lifted]] '''toward''' the [[heavens]]. (??)
#::''[[manus|Manus]] '''ad''' [[caelus|caeli]] [[templum|templa]] [[tendere|tendebam]] [[lacrimare|lacrimans]].''
#:::I [[extend]]ed my [[hand]]s '''toward''' [[heaven|heaven's]] [[temple]] [[weep]]ing.
#*::''[[w:Aeneid|Aeneid]]'' by ''[[w:Virgil|P. Vergilius Maro]]'' 
#*:::''[[duplex|Duplices]] [[tendere|tendens]] '''ad''' [[sidus|sidera]] [[palma]]s.''
#*:::: [[stretch|Stretching]] [[both]] [[hand]]s '''to''' the [[stars]].
