#:: ''[[altitudo|Altitudo]] [[pertingere|pertingit]] '''ad''' [[caelus|caelum]].''

====Related terms====
*[[ad-]] (same word modified and used as a prefix)

====Usage notes====
*The word '''ad''' is an [[antithesis]] to ''[[ab#Latin|ab]]'' (just as ''[[in#Latin|in]]'' is to ''[[ex#latin|ex]]''), in a progressive order of relation, ad denotes, first, the direction toward an object; then the reaching of or attaining to it; and finally, the being at or near it.
*Often used of geographical position of a place in reference to the points of compass, with the verbs ''[[jacere]]'' (to be situated), ''[[vergere]]'' (to incline, to slope), ''[[spectare]]'' (to observe, to see) etc.:
*: ''[[Asia#Latin|Asia]] [[jacere|jacet]] '''ad''' [[meridies|meridiem]] [[et#Latin|et]] [[auster|austrum]], [[Europa#Latin|Europa]] '''ad''' [[septentrio]]nes [[et#Latin|et]] [[aquilo]]nem.''
*:: [[Asia]] [[lie]]s '''near''' [[midday]] and [[south]], [[Europe]] '''near''' [[north]] and [[north]]. (two words for north)
*: '''''Ad''' [[Attica|Atticam]] [[vergere|vergente]].''
*:: [[incline|Inclining]] '''to''' [[Attic]]. 

